parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or fails to shift gears
the vehicle stalls
the overdrive light flashes
the vehicle lunges or surges forward
the transmission slips or grinds
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear
the transmission makes a loud clunking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4-wheel drive system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The 4-wheel drive system engages or disengages unexpectedly
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
the overdrive light flashes
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle stalls or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shifter fractures or separates from the steering column
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the rear lift gate glass can cause injuries, damage to surrounding areas, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The rear lift gate glass shatters suddenly
often without warning
and can be accompanied by a loud noise. In some cases
the glass may fall out of the lift gate
causing damage to the surrounding area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lift gate hinge can cause the lift gate to fall off, leading to accidents, injuries, and damage to surrounding areas.
symptoms: The rear lift gate hinge may fracture
break
or disengage
causing the lift gate to fall off or become unstable. In some cases
the hinge may rust or corrode
leading to failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the rear panel can lead to water leaks, rust, and corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: Cracks may appear on the rear panel
often near the lift gate or window
and can be accompanied by water leaks or rust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the body mounts can lead to structural damage, compromised vehicle safety, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The body mounts may deteriorate
leading to structural damage and potentially causing the windshield to crack.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and accidents, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission may leak fluid
fail to engage properly
or cause the vehicle to stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear coil springs can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Broken or cracked rear coil springs
sagging rear suspension
loud clunking or crashing sounds while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearings can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Abnormal noise
vibration
or pulling to one side while driving
wheel bearings seizing or freezing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the body mount bushings can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Loud clunking or crashing sounds while driving
body mounts crumbling apart
soft or jelly-like body mounts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Transmission slipping or hesitation
complete loss of transmission function
transmission failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension and steering components can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Abnormal noise
vibration
or pulling to one side while driving
broken or worn-out suspension and steering components.
